The Federal Capital Territory (FCT) Minister, Muhammad Musa Bello, has been decorated with the emblem of the 2021 Armed Forces Remembrance Day celebration by the National Chairman of the Nigerian Legion, Brigadier General Adakole Jones, Akpa (Rtd). In a brief ceremony at the Minister’s office in Abuja on Tuesday, other senior members of staff of the Administration were also decorated. The FCT minister pledged the support of the FCT Administration for the success of the yearly event to celebrate Nigeria’s fallen heroes, assuring that staff and members of the public would be encouraged to wear the emblem.  The Federal Capital Territory (FCT) Minister, Muhammad Musa Bello, has been decorated with the emblem of the 2021 Armed Forces Remembrance Day celebration by the National Chairman of the Nigerian Legion, Brigadier General Adakole Jones, Akpa (Rtd). In a brief ceremony at the Minister’s office in Abuja on Tuesday, other senior members of staff of the Administration were also decorated. The FCT minister pledged the support of the FCT Administration for the success of the yearly event to celebrate Nigeria’s fallen heroes, assuring that staff and members of the public would be encouraged to wear the emblem. 